3) Create Docker file with ubuntu base image and copy file to container in tmp directory and also download tomcat tar in container
vi Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
RUN  apt update -y
COPY index.html  /tmp
ADD  https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-11/v11.0.23/bin/apache-tomcat-11.0.23.tar.gz /tmp

4) Create Docker file with ubuntu base image and copy file to /tmp and install tomcat and set working directory and Label as charan
vi Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
COPY index.html /tmp
ADD  https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-11/v11.0.23/bin/apache-tomcat-11.0.23.tar.gz  /tmp
WORKDIR /tmp
LABEL author="charan"

5) Create Docker file with base image and set environment variables and expose port application to outside is 80
vi Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
RUN apt update -y
ENV course="DevOps"
ENV trainer="charan"
EXPOSE 80

6) Create Docker file with base image and install apache2,apache2-utils and copy direcory to container and expose port and restart service anddeploy application container
vi Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
RUN  apt update -y
RUN  apt install apache2 -y
RUN  apt install apache2-utils -y
RUN  apt clean
COPY website/ /var/www/html
RUN  service apache2 restart
EXPOSE 80
CMD  ["/usr/sbin/apachectl","-D","FOREGROUND"]

7) Create Docker file with base image and Volume inside the container 
vi Dockerfile
FROM ubuntu
RUN  apt update -y
VOLUME ["volume-1"]
LABEL author="charan"

8) Create Docker file for setup tomcat and copy jenkins war file to it
vi Dockerfile
FROM tomcat:latest
ENV CATALINA_HOME=/usr/local/tomcat
RUN rm -rf $CATALINA_HOME/webapps/*
COPY jenkins.war $CATALINA_HOME/webapps/jenkins.war
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["catalina.sh","run"]

